  <p>High infant mortality rate defined as number of death per 1000 live births has been a worrying issue for India. In 2016, India's infant mortality rate was 34, which is half of what it was in 2000.</p>

  <p>The rate has gone down consitently each year, showing that the issue of healthcare has been the primary focus of each government.

