  <p>Although the rate is going down, it is still a high number. Infant mortality rate in the United States is as low as 5.8, according to Center for Disease Control and Prevention. In comparison, India's rate is around 6 times more than the United States.</p>

  <p>Critics and experts say that India needs to invest more in the rural healthcare system and education. An analysis of the data suggests that infant mortality rate depends on literacy and expenditure.</p>

  
